BofA Insurance Banker Littlejohn Hired by BMO Capital Markets

-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r   a n d   Z a c h a r y   M i d e r
-- 
2011-05-19T21:29:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/bofa-insurance-banker-littlejohn-hired-by-bmo-capital-markets.html
BMO Capital Markets hired investment
banker Scott Littlejohn from  Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  to expand its
U.S. insurance coverage  Littlejohn will work at BMO Capital Markets’ New York
office, Beja Rodeck, a spokeswoman for the firm, said today in
an e-mail. Littlejohn was a managing director at Bank of
America’s financial institutions investment-banking group since
2007. He previously spent 15 years at  Citigroup Inc. (C)   BMO Capital Markets is the investment banking business of
 Bank of Montreal (BMO) , Canada’s fourth-biggest bank.  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
David Scanlan at   dscanlan@bloomberg.net ;
David Scheer at   dscheer@bloomberg.net  